# Data Storage

All downloaded report data is stored in **SQLite** at `data/amazon.db`.

## Never save raw JSON files as the final output

After downloading a report, insert into the database — don't write a standalone `.json` file.

## Standard pattern

```python
import sqlite3

DB_PATH = 'data/amazon.db'

with sqlite3.connect(DB_PATH) as conn:
    conn.execute('''CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS sqp_report (
        id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
        marketplace TEXT,
        asin TEXT,
        start_date TEXT,
        end_date TEXT,
        search_query TEXT,
        search_query_score INTEGER,
        search_query_volume INTEGER,
        total_impressions INTEGER,
        asin_impressions INTEGER,
        asin_impression_share REAL,
        total_clicks INTEGER,
        asin_clicks INTEGER,
        asin_click_share REAL,
        total_cart_adds INTEGER,
        asin_cart_adds INTEGER,
        total_purchases INTEGER,
        asin_purchases INTEGER,
        downloaded_at TEXT
    )''')
    conn.executemany('INSERT INTO sqp_report (...) VALUES (...)', rows)
```

## Database location

`data/amazon.db` — committed to `.gitignore`, never to source control.
